/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≅ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≅ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
theorem hom_congr_symm_apply (k : Type _) {C : Type _} [Category C] [Semiring k] [Preadditive C] [Linear k C]
    {X Y W Z : C} (f₁ : «expr ≅ » X Y) (f₂ : «expr ≅ » W Z) (f : «expr ⟶ » Y Z) :
    (homCongr k f₁ f₂).symm f = «expr ≫ » f₁.hom («expr ≫ » f f₂.inv) :=
  rfl
#align hom_congr_symm_apply hom_congr_symm_apply

-- (the linter doesn't like `simp` on the `_assoc` lemma)
theorem hom_congr_apply (k : Type _) {C : Type _} [Category C] [Semiring k] [Preadditive C] [Linear k C] {X Y W Z : C}
    (f₁ : «expr ≅ » X Y) (f₂ : «expr ≅ » W Z) (f : «expr ⟶ » X W) :
    homCongr k f₁ f₂ f = «expr ≫ » («expr ≫ » f₁.inv f) f₂.hom :=
  rfl
#align hom_congr_apply hom_congr_apply
